Question with Dependency Injection

16 minutes ago duckkiller53 LINK

Could someone help.

I have an interface called IDataService that contains four methods. 1. AdObject 2. UpdateObject 3. DeleteObject 4. DeleteObjectByID. I then created a class "AuditService" which implements IDataService. Next I have a class "DataLayer" which via Dependency Injection, takes a class of type IDataService in it's constructor. My goal is to have a general class that I can plug multiple service classes into and avoid dependencies.

The problem I'm having is this. I need to add additional methods to the different service classes ie: in this case the "AuditService" class that are unique to this module. The problem I'm having is the added methods that are not implemented as part of the IDataService interface are not showing up when I instantiate the DataLayer class. I have added a property in DataLayer that returns the service class that it was instantiated with thinking that would expose the added methods of AuditService. But it does not. Is there a way to do this. Again, "How do you expose methods of a class that are added beyond the scope of the interface which it impliments?

Any Help would be very appreaciated.

Thank You

public interface IDataService { bool AddObject<T>(ref T obj); bool UpdateObject<T>(T obj); bool DeleteObject<T>(T obj); bool DeleteObjectByID(int id); }

public class AuditService : IDataService { #region Declarations public const string ASCENDING = "asc"; public const string DESCENDING = "desc"; public const int DEFAULT_VALUE = 0; #endregion

#region Methods

public System.Collections.Generic.IEnumerable<Audit> GetAuditSearch(string sorttype,  string sortfield, string sortdir, string search) { }

public IEnumerable<Audit> GetAudits(string sortfield, string sortdir) { }

public virtual Audit GetAuditByID(int id){ }

public bool AddObject<T>(ref T obj){ }

public bool UpdateObject<T>(T obj) { }

public bool DeleteObject<T>(T obj){ }

public bool DeleteObjectByID(int value) { }

#endregion }

public class DataLayer { #region "Declarations"

private IDataService _service; protected static string _ConnStr = ConfigurationManager.ConnectionStrings["program"].ConnectionString;

#endregion

#region Properties public SqlConnection ProgramConn { }

/// <summary> /// Use to call specific methods /// </summary> public IDataService Methods { get { return _service; } }

#endregion

#region Constructors public DataLayer(IDataService service) { this._service = service; }

#endregion

#region Methods

public bool AddObject<T>(ref T obj) { return this._service.AddObject(ref obj); }

public bool UpdateObject<T>(T obj) { return this._service.UpdateObject(obj); }

public bool DeleteObject<T>(T obj) { return this._service.DeleteObject(obj); }

public bool DeleteObjectByID(int id) { return this._service.DeleteObjectByID(id); } #endregion }

// SAMPLE IMPLIMENTATION OF DataLayer

public static bool DeleteAuditByID(int id) { DataLayer d = new DataLayer(new AuditService()); return d.DeleteObjectByID(id); }

